WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:05.670 --> 00:00:14.400
Cut the chicken into small chunks. 

00:00:15.600 --> 00:00:21.930
Finely chop the onion.

00:00:23.130 --> 00:00:34.300
Coarsely chop the carrot and the bell pepper.

00:00:35.670 --> 00:00:42.530
Heat the oil in a non-stick frying pan and sauté the chicken until the color changes. 

00:00:43.730 --> 00:00:48.330
Add the carrot and the onion. 

00:00:49.530 --> 00:01:04.300
When the vegetables are thoroughly cooked, add the bell pepper and, season with the salt, the pepper, the ketchup, and the Worcestershire sauce.

00:01:05.500 --> 00:01:18.230
Mix in the rice and sauté and then remove the mixture and divide into two portions. 

00:01:19.600 --> 00:01:29.300
Beat the eggs in a bowl and mix in the nagaimo, the milk and the salt.

00:01:30.670 --> 00:01:39.400
Melt the butter in a non-stick frying pan and pour in the egg mixture.

00:01:40.600 --> 00:01:48.370
Place the rice on the egg and gently wrap with the egg. 

00:01:49.570 --> 00:01:54.470
Transfer the rice omelet into a plate, squirt ketchup on top and garnish with the parsley.

